candidates.title: Human sort channel list
candidates.body:
https://crates.io/search?q=human-sort tells that `human-sort` total number of downloads is 170k, so seems to be a popular crate.

Fixes #683.

candidates.title: Host crate on Cargo: tag `julia` as binary name for `julialauncher`
candidates.body:
This creates `julia` as another executable for `julialauncher` in the cargo bin folder. Thus allowing you to install `juliaup` from crates.io and have a working `julia` command.

Fixes #618. Note that `julialauncher` will still appear in the `bin` folder.

You can test this out by running:

```
cargo install --git https://github.com/MilesCranmer/juliaup.git --branch rust-pkg
```
and verifying that `juliaup` and `julia` are installed in the cargo binary folder.

@davidanthoff feel free to push to this PR

candidates.title: MSI Installer
candidates.body: Fallback option where MSIX doesn't work (Windows Server primarily).

candidates.title: Add support for directory overrides
candidates.body:
This adds an `override` command to `juliaup`:

- `juliaup override set lts`: Sets an override for the current directory to the `lts` channel.
- `juliaup override unset`: Removes an override for the current directory.
- `juliaup override status`: Shows all overrides.

There are some more options, see the command line help for those.

candidates.title: Modify startup scripts as byte vectors instead of strings
candidates.body: This PR is intended to fix #433 by matching on and replacing pure byte streams. This way, the assumption of valid UTF-8 data in the startup files is loosened. A typical case where this could cause issues is when operating system paths that are not valid UTF-8 data are used.

candidates.title: Configure for target_os, not nonexistant family

milestone.title: Release as official Julia version manager

candidates.body:
`cfg(macos)` is invalid, because `macos` is not a target family, but a target os. This causes the cfg to be ignored.
See more here:
https://rust-lang.github.io/rust-clippy/master/index.html#mismatched_target_os
